Virtual Machine is  an emulator of a computer system (Wikipedia) providing an independent place to run programs.
Vagrant is open-source software used to manage and build virtual environments. 
Mitchell  Hashimoto wrote Vagrant.
Ubuntu is an opensource operating system.
Ubuntu is a Nguni word that refers to humanity and compassion.
Using Vagrant with VMs: once a Vagrantfile is created members of the same project team can work on the project in the same environment.
Uname prinst the system information.  For instance whwn I typed in uname in the Terminal after accessing loading and accessing Vagrant "Linux" appeared because I was using a linux system.
A Zero-Day refers to the day when "interested part(ies)" becaome aware of their vulnerabilities.
